Package: unitar
Title: Share targets across projects and users
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(person("Nathan", "Sheffield", email = "nathan@code.databio.org",role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: A a simple R package that wraps the targets package. 
	It provides functionality to use targets that span projects, which is outside the scope of the base targets package. With unitar, you can link two targets projects and load targets from external projects so that you can share caches and computing across users and projects.
License: BSD_2_clause + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: targets, fs, withr
Imports: pepr
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0), knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
URL: https://github.com/databio/unitar
BugReports: https://github.com/databio/unitar
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
